23/12/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Organisation for Security and Co-operation in Europe (OSCE) will complete its mission in Croatia on December 31st, after 11 years in the country, OSCE spokesperson Ljerka Drazenovic announced on Friday (December 21st). The decision was made after the OSCE headquarters in Vienna made an assessment of Croatia's democratic development. The current mission will be replaced by an office that will monitor the return of Serb fugitives and will work on war crimes cases in local courts. (AFP, HRT, RTRS, SRNA, Makfax - 22/12/07)
